    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sanctae et individuae trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king #Monasteries #Imperial/royal_diploma #Immunity #Islands #Churches #Curtes #Landed_possessions #Mansi #Forests #Castle #Tolls #Ports #Decima #Hospitals" ref="#people/124"
                            >Fridericus</persName> divina favente clementia Romanorum <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> et semper augustus. Habemus in
                        exemplis antecessorum nostrorum regum et imperatorum, quod ex imperiali
                        sollicitudine omnibus fidelibus imperii debeamus providere, maxime vero ad
                        tutelam ecclesiarum Dei, quae sub nostra dominatione retinentur, dexteram
                        defensionis extendere debeamus, quia, si in sanctuario dei praeter id, quod
                        ab aliis positum est, nos quoque aliquid supererogaverimus, a vero
                        Samaritano, cum redierit, nobis in centuplum esse reddendum speramus et
                        credimus. Eapropter cognoscant universi fideles imperii per Italiam
                        constituti praesentes et futuri, quod nos pro nostra nostrorumque
                        antecessorum perpetua salute <orgName key="#Abbots #Monasteries #Imperial/royal_diploma #Monks #Immunity #Islands #Churches #Curtes #Landed_possessions #Mansi #Forests #Castle #Tolls #Ports #Decima #Hospitals" ref="#juridical_persons/2001"><rs
                                key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs> sancti Benedicti situm inter
                            <placeName ref="#places/4196">Padum</placeName> et <placeName
                                ref="#places/4197">Larionem</placeName></orgName>, venerabilem
                        quoque <rs key="#Abbots">abbatem</rs>
                        <persName key="#Abbots #Monasteries #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4058">Victorem</persName> et eius fratres et <rs key="#Monks"
                            >monachos</rs> et omnia eiusdern monasterii bona mobilia et immobilia
                        intus et foris sub nostram imperialem defensionem ac protectionem suscipimus
                        omnesque praedicti monasterii possessiones, quas in presenti iuste habet vel
                        in posterum deo iuvante rationabiliter acquirere poterit, nostra imperiali
                        auctoritate ipsi monasterio concedimus et confirmamus, sicut in authenticis
                        antecessorum nostrorum regum et imperatorum <rs
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">privilegiis</rs> continetur, videlicet
                            <placeName key="#Islands #Churches" ref="#places/2400"><rs
                                key="#Islands">insulam</rs> sancti Benedicti</placeName> cum <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Islands #Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2058">sancti
                            Floriani</orgName> et eius pertinentiis, <placeName
                            key="#Islands #Churches" ref="#places/2402">insulam quae vocatur
                            Gurgo</placeName>, cum <orgName key="#Islands #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2059">ecclesia eiusdem insulae</orgName> et suis
                        pertinentiis, <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/2931">Casale
                            Barbatum</placeName> cum ecclesia <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2062">sanctae Mariae</orgName> et <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2063">sancti Laurentii</orgName>
                        earumque pertinentiis, <placeName key="#Churches #Tolls #Ports"
                            ref="#places/2476">Septingentum</placeName> cum <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2064">ecclesia sancti Michaelis</orgName>
                        eiusque pertinentiis et cum <rs key="#Tolls">ripatico</rs> de <rs
                            key="#Ports">transitu navium</rs>, decimam partem <rs key="#Curtes"
                            >curtis</rs>, quae vocatur <geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/2050"
                            >Burbassium</geogName>, cum <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2003">ecclesia sancti Ioannis</orgName> suisque
                        pertinentiis, locum, qui vocatur <placeName ref="#places/624"
                            >Nucetula</placeName>, <orgName key="#Hospitals"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2077"><rs key="#Hospitals">domum hospitalis</rs>
                            apud <placeName key="#Hospitals #Bishops" ref="#places/275"
                                >Mantuam</placeName></orgName> cum suis pertinentiis, <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2067">ecclesiam sancti
                            Valentini</orgName> de <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/2932"
                            >Maringo</placeName> cum suis pertinentiis, <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2066">ecclesiam sancti Viti</orgName> de
                            <placeName key="#Churches #Landed_possessions" ref="#places/2475"
                            >Medula</placeName> cum suis pertinentiis et <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terras</rs>, quas praedictum monasterium ibi
                        possidet, <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2074">ecclesiam
                            sancti Michaelis</orgName> de <placeName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#places/2936">Cotorlione</placeName> cum suis pertinentiis,
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2068">ecclesiam sancti
                                Benedicti</orgName> apud <placeName key="#Churches #Landed_possessions" ref="#places/77"
                            >Figarolum</placeName> et <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2098">ecclesiam sanctae Agathae</orgName> apud
                            <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/80">Ferrariam</placeName> cum
                        ambarum pertinentiis, <orgName key="#Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2075">monasterium sancti Cipriani</orgName> apud
                            <placeName>Venetiam</placeName> cum suis pertinentiis, <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2076">ecclesiam sanctae
                            Helene</orgName> apud <placeName>Thessariam</placeName> cum suis
                        pertinentiis, <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/2969"
                            >Concam</placeName> cum <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2099">ecclesia sancti Leonardi</orgName> et suis
                        pertinentiis, locum, qui dicitur <placeName key="#Churches #Decima"
                            ref="#places/2970">Focculare</placeName>, cum <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2490">ecclesia sancti Marci</orgName> et omnibus
                            <rs key="#Decima">decimis</rs> eiusdem loci, <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2006">ecclesias sancti Benedicti</orgName> et
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2080">sanctae
                            Mariae</orgName> apud <placeName key="#Churches #Decima"
                            ref="#places/2414">Gonzagam</placeName> cum omnibus decimis eiusdem loci
                        et certis pertinentiis, <placeName ref="#places/2929">Caput
                        Uici</placeName>, <placeName key="#Churches #Decima" ref="#places/362"
                            >Uillulam</placeName> cum <orgName key="#Churches #Decima"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2079">ecclesia sanctae Mariae</orgName> et
                        omnibus decimis et suis pertinentiis, <placeName key="#Churches #Decima"
                            ref="#places/2417">Quistellum</placeName> cum <orgName
                            key="#Churches #Decima" ref="#juridical_persons/2054">ecclesia sancti
                            Bartholornei</orgName> et omnibus decimis eiusdem loci, <placeName
                            key="#Churches #Decima" ref="#places/2930">Babianum</placeName> cum
                            <orgName key="#Churches #Decima" ref="#juridical_persons/2060">ecclesia
                            sancti Andreae</orgName> et omnibus decimis eiusdem loci, <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2061">ecclesiam sancti
                            Venerii</orgName> de <placeName key="#Churches #Castle"
                            ref="#places/2900">Marzeneta</placeName> cum medietate eiusdem <rs
                            key="#Castle">castri</rs> et suis pertinentiis, <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2074">ecclesiam sancti Michaelis</orgName> de
                            <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/2935">Telione</placeName> cum
                        suis pertinerntiis, <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2090"
                            >ecclesiam sancti Bartholomei</orgName> de <placeName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#places/4">Lucca</placeName> cum suis pertinentiis, <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2087">sanctum Martinum Vicellae</orgName> cum
                        suis pertinentiis, <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2071"
                            >ecclesiam sancti Leonardi</orgName> apud <placeName
                            key="#Dioecesis #Churches #Mother_churches #Comitatus" ref="#places/53"
                            >Parmam</placeName> et omnia, quae praedictum monasterium in <orgName
                            key="#Dioecesis #Mother_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/1420">eodem
                                <rs key="#Dioecesis #Mother_churches">episcopatu</rs></orgName>
                        tenet, <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2081">ecclesiam
                            sancti Xisti</orgName> de <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/361"
                            >Lecto Paludano</placeName>, <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2069">ecclesias sanctae Mariae</orgName> et
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2070">sancti
                            Ioannis</orgName> in <orgName
                            key="#Dioecesis #Churches #Mother_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/80"
                            >episcopatu <placeName key="#Dioecesis #Churches #Mother_churches"
                                ref="#places/7">Bononiensi</placeName></orgName> cum suis
                        pertinentiis, decimas de <placeName key="#Decima" ref="#places/2972">Runcis
                            Gunthardi</placeName>, <orgName key="#Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2414">monasterium sanctae Mariae de <placeName
                                key="#Monasteries" ref="#places/4105">Pratalia</placeName></orgName>
                        cum suis pertinentiis, <orgName key="#Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2420">monasterium sanctae Crucis de <placeName
                                key="#Monasteries" ref="#places/4108">Campo
                            Syon</placeName></orgName> cum suis pertinentiis, <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/2473">monasterium sanctorum
                            Firmi et Rustici</orgName> cum suis pertinentiis, <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2463">ecclesiam sanctae
                            Christine</orgName> de <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/2942"
                                >Bardulino</placeName> cum suis pertinentiis, <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/1469"
                                    >ecclesiam sancti Cesarii</orgName> cum tota <geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/155">curte</geogName>
                        et suis pertinentiis de <placeName key="#Curtes #Churches" ref="#places/269">Guizacara</placeName> cum bonis, quac <rs
                            key="#Countess">comitissa</rs>
                        <persName key="#Countess" ref="#people/125">Mathildis</persName> pro anima
                        sua eidem ecclesiae contulit. <geogName key="#Forests" ref="#estates/2094"><rs key="#Forests">Buscos</rs> quoque de
                            <placeName key="#Forests" ref="#places/34">Pigugnaga</placeName></geogName> cum omnibus, quae
                        <persName key="#Forests" ref="#people/3707">Hugizo</persName> in pignore habuit et tenuit. Octo etiam
                        <rs key="#Mansi">mansos</rs> in <geogName key="#Mansi #Landed_possessions" ref="#estates/77">villa quae dicitur Lectus
                            Palludanus</geogName> una cum tribus agris cellulisque adiacentibus,
                        terras etiam, quas praedictum monasterium tenet in <geogName
                            key="#Iudiciaria #Landed_possessions" ref="#estates/2076"><rs
                                key="#Iudiciaria">Iudicaria</rs> Gardense</geogName> seu in toto
                            <geogName key="#Comitatus #Landed_possessions" ref="#estates/124"><rs
                                key="#Comitatus">comitatu</rs>
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus #Landed_possessions" ref="#places/59"
                                >Ueronensi</placeName></geogName>, terras quoque, quas iamdictum
                        monasteriurn tenet in <placeName key="#Landed_possessions" ref="#places/2410">Monticulo</placeName> et in
                        <placeName key="#Landed_possessions" ref="#places/2971">Birruto</placeName>. Universa insuper, quae et a felicis
                        memoriae Mathildae comitissa et a <rs key="#Count">comite</rs>
                        <persName key="#Count" ref="#people/3571">Alberto</persName> seu ab aliis
                        quibuscumque de praediis, quae fuerint eiusdem comitissae, praedicto
                        monasterio aut iam collata sunt aut in posterum deo largiente quoquo iusto
                        modo conferri vel acquiri contigerit, quicquid etiam habet et possidet in
                        <placeName>Portu</placeName> et in <placeName ref="#places/4450">Legnago</placeName> et braidam de <placeName key="#Landed_possessions" ref="#places/4449">Magarino</placeName>, in Figarolo et aliam braidam,
                        quam dedit <persName><name ref="Rotarius/de Quistello"></name>Rotheherius de Quistello</persName> cum aliis terris. Ras omnes praedictas
                        possessiones, quae praefato monasterio concessae sunt et per authentica
                        praedecessorum nostrorum regum et imperatorum privilegia confirmatae, nos
                        quoque eidem monasterio benigne concedimus et auctoritate privilegii
                        imperialis confirmmnus salva per omnia imperiali iustitia. Adicientes itaque
                        ex imperiali edicto statuimus et firmiter precipimus, <rs key="#Immunity">ut
                            in praedictis bonis ipsius monasterii nullus archiepiscopus, non
                            episcopus, non dux, nec marchio nec comes aut vicecomes, nulla civitas,
                            nulla persona secularis vel ecclesiastica magna vel parva praedictum
                            abbatem Victorem vel eius monachos vel etiam praefati monasterii homines
                            aliquo modo molestare vel inquietare vel disvestire audeat per aliquam
                            albergariam sive collectam aut ullam exactionem aliquo tempore in ipsis
                            bonis facere praesumat nec aliquis hominum ullam potestatem supra
                            praefatum monasterium habeat nisi solus Romanus imperator</rs>.
                        Praeterea quoniam in ore religiosorum et ministrorum Christi non debet
                        inveniri mendatium, ipsam domum beati Benedicti eiusque fratres et monachos
                        a lege et sacramento calumnie absolvimus et omnino liberos dimittimus.
                        Quodsi aliquis contra hoc nostrae largitionis et confirmationis praeceptum
                        facere praesumpserit, sciat se <rs key="#Penalty">centum libras auri
                            optimi</rs> pro paena compositurum, dimidium <rs key="#Camera_regis"
                            >fisco nostro</rs> et dimidium praedicto abbati et eius monasterio.
                        Huius rei <rs key="#Witness">testes</rs> sunt: <persName
                            key="#Bishops #Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4047"
                            >Cunradus</persName>
                        <placeName key="#Bishops" ref="#places/2968">Magontinus</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">electus</rs>, <persName ref="#people/4030"
                            >Garsendonius</persName> Mantuanus episcopus, <persName
                                key="#Abbots #Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4050">Hermannus</persName>
                        <orgName key="#Abbots" ref="#juridical_persons/2479"><placeName
                                key="#Abbots" ref="#places/4422">Hersfeldensis</placeName></orgName>
                        abbas, <persName key="#Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4051">Vlricus dux
                            Boemiae</persName>, <persName key="#Palatine_count #Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4052"
                            >Otto <rs key="#Palatine_count">palatinus</rs> iunior de Witelinesbach</persName>, comes <persName
                                key="#Count #Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4053">Conradus de
                            Leuerstein</persName>, comes <persName
                                key="#Count #Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4054">Wernherus de
                                Hohemberch</persName>, <persName key="#Other_palatine_officer #Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4055"
                            >Henricus <rs key="#Other_palatine_officer">marischalcus</rs></persName>, <persName
                                key="#Other_palatine_officer #Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4056">Cunradus <rs key="#Other_palatine_officer">pincerna</rs></persName>,
                        <persName key="#Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4057">Cunradus de
                            Balnhusen</persName> et alii quam plures. Signum domini Federici
                        Romanorum imperatoris invictissimi. Ego <persName
                            key="#Chancellor #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4048"
                            >Christianus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> vice <persName
                            key="#Archbishops #Archchancellor #Imperial/royal_diploma"
                            ref="#people/4049">Reinaldi</persName>
                        <placeName key="#Archbishops" ref="#places/1850">Colloniensis</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovi. Acta sunt haec anno dominice
                        incarnationis MCLXIIII, indictione XII, regnante domino Federico Romanorum
                        imperatore gloriosissimo, anno regni eius XII, imperii vero VIII; datum apud
                            <placeName ref="#places/3513">Faventiam</placeName> nonis ianuariii. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
